## M20a negative: method body type error.
##
## Before M20a, method bodies weren't sema-checked (M12 emit-only).
## M20a's `ExprChecker.walkMethod` now type-checks the body against
## the declared return type. A `String`-returning method whose body
## yields `Int` must error.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error: `incompatible types ...` at the body.

struct User
  name: String

  fun greet(self: ?User) -> String
    42

sub main()
  u = User(name: "Steve")
  print(u.greet())
